38 SECTION 3.
39 Article 10 of Chapter 3 of Title 38 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
40 state-wide first responder building mapping information system, is amended by adding a new
41 paragraph to Code Section 38-3-151, relating to definitions, as follows:
42 "(4) 'School mapping data' means building information, floor plans, and aerial imagery
43 of any public or private school."
44 SECTION 4.
45 Said article is further amended by adding a new Code section to read as follows:
46 "38-3-154.
47 (a) Not later than July 1, 2026, each local school system shall procure school mapping data
48 for each public and private school within its boundaries.
49 (b) The school mapping data required in subsection (a) of this Code section shall:
50 (1) Be in formats that conform to and integrate with software platforms utilized in local
51 public safety answering points and by local, state, and federal public safety agencies that
52 respond to emergencies at schools and that do not require such agencies to purchase
53 additional software or provide payment in order to view or access such data;
54 (2) Be in formats capable of being printed, shared electronically, and, if requested,
55 digitally integrated into interactive mobile platforms;
56 (3) Be verified for accuracy by July 1 each year by the entity producing such school
57 mapping data by means of an in-person inspection of each school;
58 (4) Identify and label access points of each building interior, including, but not limited
59 to, rooms, doors, stairwells, and hallways, each of which shall include any identifiers or
60 names utilized by staff and students;
61 (5) Identify and label locations of critical utilities, key boxes, automated external
62 defibrillators, and trauma kits or other emergency response aids; and
