63 (6) Identify and label areas at or near each school, including parking areas, athletic fields,
64 surrounding roads, outbuildings, and neighboring properties.
65 (c) Any future updates to school mapping data provided for in this Code section shall
66 conform to and integrate with software platforms utilized in local public safety answering
67 points and by local, state, and federal public safety agencies that provide emergency
68 services to each school.
69 (d) The agency shall be authorized to develop rules and regulations for the requirements
70 for school mapping data, including, but not limited to, standards for the use of school
71 mapping data, encryption of such data, and transmission of such data over secure methods
72 to law enforcement officers, firefighters, and other authorized emergency first responders.
73 (e) Information provided to the agency under this Code section shall be exempt from
74 public disclosure to the extent provided in Code Section 50-18-72.
75 (f)(1) Local boards of education, local school systems, and local governments and
76 agencies shall be immune from civil liability for any damages arising out of the creation
77 and use of the school mapping data.
78 (2) Employees of local boards of education, local school systems, and local governments
79 and agencies shall be immune from civil liability for any damages arising out of the
80 creation and use of the school mapping data unless it is shown that such employee acted
81 with gross negligence or bad faith."
82 SECTION 5.
83 This Act shall become effective July 1, 2025.
84 SECTION 6.
85 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
